  "prompt": "I keep getting dock connected on my Android, how do I get it off?",
  "response": "To resolve the \"dock connected\" issue on your Android device, try these steps:\n\n1. Basic troubleshooting:\n- Check for physical debris in the charging port\n- Restart your phone\n- Clean the charging port gently with compressed air\n\n2. Software-related solutions:\n- Go to Settings > Connected devices\n- Check for any active dock connections\n- Disconnect or forget the dock\n\n3. If using a case:\n- Remove the phone case\n- Ensure no case accessories are interfering with connection\n\n4. Check USB settings:\n- Go to Settings > Developer options\n- Look for USB configuration settings\n- Reset to default\n\n5. If problem persists:\n- Check for system updates\n- Reset device to factory settings (backup data first)\n- Contact manufacturer support\n\n6. Hardware potential solutions:\n- If charging port is damaged, consider professional repair\n- Use original charger and cables\n\nIf none of these work, consider:\n- Visiting an authorized service center\n- Consulting your phone manufacturer's support\n\nWould you like me to elaborate on any of these steps?",
